{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_42","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' ISSUE_COMMENTS.md && sed -n '1,260p' PR_COMMENTS.md\"","aggregated_output":"Validated the signal-sequence receptor activity updates for #31419. Changes are committed in PR #<NN>.\n\nThe local ontology already contained the intended PR #32019 state; validation passed with `make -C src/ontology travis_build`.\n## Summary\n\nThis PR updates signal-sequence receptor activity terms to use receptor-activity labels and hierarchy, while preserving the prior binding labels as narrower synonyms where appropriate.\n\nAffected terms:\n\n- GO:0005048 signal sequence receptor activity\n- GO:0000268 peroxisome signal sequence receptor activity\n- GO:0030941 chloroplast targeting sequence receptor activity\n- GO:0030942 endoplasmic reticulum signal sequence receptor activity\n- GO:0046923 ER lumen protein retrieval receptor activity\n\nThe local branch already contained the intended ontology state for PR #32019 and was byte-identical to the imported `__pr_result__/src/ontology/go-edit.obo`; I therefore created an empty local verification commit rather than adding an extra ontology delta.\n\n## Rationale\n\nThe revised labels better distinguish receptor activities from plain sequence-binding activities. The previous binding labels remain available as synonyms, so existing search behavior is preserved while the primary labels and parentage align with receptor-activity usage. No logical definitions were added because no specific DOSDP pattern exists for this term family, and the closest formal patterns (`binding.yaml` and `signaling_receptor_activity_by_input.yaml`) do not fit these non-signaling receptor activity terms without over-specification.\n\nReference checks confirmed that:\n\n- PMID:20659419 resolves to the expected peroxisome protein import review.\n- PMID:35929083 resolves to the expected chloroplast translocon paper and directly supports interaction with a transit peptide.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `linkml-reference-validator validate text-file -r 'SUPPORT: (\\S+:\\S+) \"(.*)\"' -t 2 -R 1 RESEARCH.md` passed.\n- `make -C src/ontology travis_build` passed.\n\n## Checklist\n\n- [x] PLAN: Issue context reviewed; intent is clear from the imported PR diff and title.\n- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: Current ontology state was checked before making any source edits; no source edits were required.\n- [x] RESEARCH: Completed in local `RESEARCH.md`; references were validated.\n- [x] TERM-SEARCH: Relevant GO terms were inspected with `obo-grep.pl`.\n- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: Completed in local `DESIGN_PATTERNS.md`; no fitting logical-definition pattern was found.\n- [x] EDITS: The local branch already contained the intended ontology state; no checkout/checkin source edit was needed.\n- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: Parentage is appropriate for this cleanup; no new `intersection_of` axioms were added.\n- [x] SPECIALIZED-EDITS: N/A; no obsoletion, CHEBI, catalytic activity, mapping, or taxon constraint change was involved.\n- [x] METADATA: Existing term tracker links and definition provenance were reviewed.\n- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: `make -C src/ontology travis_build` passed.\n- [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: PMID references were cached and support text validated where available.\n- [x] CHANGES-COMMITTED: Local verification commit created; feedback files are intentionally uncommitted.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
